scooter rent \u2013 \u20b9\u202f400\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f800** <br> (fuel \u2248 \u20b9\u202f150) \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f950** | 2\u2011day scooter rent \u2013 \u20b9\u202f400\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f800** <br> Airport\u2011hotel taxi (round\u2011trip) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f500 \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f2\u202f300** | 2\u2011day premium scooter (Royal Enfield) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f800\u202f/\u202fday \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f1\u202f600** <br> Airport\u2011hotel limo (round\u2011trip) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f3\u202f000 \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f4\u202f600** |\\n| **Attractions & Activities** | \u2022 Dolphin\u2011watch (optional) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 <br>\u2022 Fort Aguada entry \u2013 free <br>\u2022 Beach shacks (water sports) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f500 <br>**Total** \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f1\u202f700** | \u2022 Dolphin\u2011watch \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 <br>\u2022 Fort Aguada entry \u2013 free <br>\u2022 Water sports (parasailing, jet\u2011ski) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200 <br>\u2022 Sunset cruise \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f500 <br>**Total** \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f3\u202f900** | \u2022 Private dolphin\u2011watch + breakfast on boat \u2013 \u20b9\u202f2\u202f500 <br>\u2022 Fort Aguada entry \u2013 free <br>\u2022 Full\u2011day water\u2011sports package (jet\u2011ski, banana boat, windsurf) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f3\u202f000 <br>\u2022 Sunset yacht cruise with canap\u00e9s \u2013 \u20b9\u202f4\u202f500 <br>**Total** \u2192 **\u20b9\u202f10\u202f000** |\\n| **Miscellaneous** (tips, souvenirs, Wi\u2011Fi) | \u20b9\u202f500 | \u20b9\u202f1\u202f000 | \u20b9\u202f2\u202f000 |\\n| **Grand Total (per person)** | **\u20b9\u202f6\u202f350** | **\u20b9\u202f20\u202f000** | **\u20b9\u202f55\u202f200** |\\n\\n> **Result:**  \\n> \u2022 The **budget** and **mid\u2011range** plans sit comfortably under the \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 ceiling.  \\n> \u2022 The **luxury** version exceeds it by ~\u20b9\u202f5\u202f200; you can trim it by swapping the yacht cruise for a sunset beach dinner or choosing a slightly cheaper 5\u2011star resort (e.g., Alila \u2013 \u20b9\u202f12\u202f000/night) to bring it back under \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000.\\n\\nBelow is a **day\u2011by\u2011day schedule** that works for any of the three tiers \u2013 just swap the hotel, food and activity levels accordingly.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Day\u202f1 \u2013 Arrival & South\u2011Goa Highlights  \\n\\n| Time | Activity | Details |\\n|------|----------|---------|\\n| **08:00 \u2013 09:30** | **Arrival at Dabolim Airport** | Pre\u2011book a taxi/limo (see transport column). |\\n| **09:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Check\u2011in & Freshen up** | Drop luggage, quick shower. |\\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:30** | **Relax at Colva / Benaulim Beach** | Sunbathe, dip in sea, optional beach\u2011side yoga (\u20b9\u202f200). |\\n| **12:30 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch** | *Budget*: Fisherman\u2019s Wharf (Goan thali, \u20b9\u202f300). <br>*Mid*: Martin\u2019s Corner (seafood platter, \u20b9\u202f600). <br>*Luxury*: The Fisherman\u2019s Wharf \u2013 private table, \u20b9\u202f1\u202f500. |\\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:30** | **Fort Aguada & Lighthouse** | Free entry, great photo ops. |\\n| **15:30 \u2013 16:30** | **Coffee break** | Beach shack (coconut water, coffee \u2013 \u20b9\u202f150). |\\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:30** | **Dolphin\u2011watch (optional)** | Boat departs from Sinquerim. <br> *Budget*: Group boat \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200. <br> *Mid*: Semi\u2011private \u2013 \u20b9\u202f1\u202f500. <br> *Luxury*: Private charter \u2013 \u20b9\u202f2\u202f500. |\\n| **19:00 \u2013 20:30** | **Sunset at Candolim Beach** | Walk along the shore, snap sunset pics. |\\n| **20:30 \u2013 22:00** | **Dinner** | *Budget*: Beach shack (fish fry, rice, \u20b9\u202f400). <br>*Mid*: Thalassa (Greek\u2011Goan fusion, \u20b9\u202f1\u202f000). <br>*Luxury*: The Leela\u2019s Sea\u2011View Restaurant, \u20b9\u202f2\u202f500. |\\n| **22:30** | **Back to hotel / Nightlife** | If you\u2019re up for it, head to **Tito\u2019s** (Baga) or **Mambo\u2019s** for a quick drink (\u20b9\u202f300\u2011\u20b9\u202f600). |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Day\u202f2 \u2013 North\u2011Goa Adventure & Departure  \\n\\n| Time | Activity | Details |\\n|------|----------|---------|\\n| **07:30 \u2013 08:30** | **Breakfast** | *Budget*: Hostel kitchen (\u20b9\u202f0) or caf\u00e9 (\u20b9\u202f150). <br>*Mid*: Hotel buffet (\u20b9\u202f300). <br>*Luxury*: Leela\u2019s breakfast spread (\u20b9\u202f800). |\\n| **08:30 \u2013 10:30** | **Calangute & Baga Beaches** | Try parasailing (\u20b9\u202f800) or just stroll. |\\n| **10:30 \u2013 12:00** | **Shopping at Anjuna Flea Market** | Souvenirs, beachwear \u2013 budget \u20b9\u202f500\u2011\u20b9\u202f1\u202f000. |\\n| **12:00 \u2013 13:30** | **Lunch** | *Budget*: Suzie\u2019s (Goan veg thali, \u20b9\u202f250). <br>*Mid*: Britto\u2019s (seafood, \u20b9\u202f800). <br>*Luxury*: Beachfront fine\u2011dining at Park Hyatt (\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000). |\\n| **13:30 \u2013 15:30** | **Water\u2011Sports Package** | *Budget*: Simple jet\u2011ski (\u20b9\u202f500). <br>*Mid*: Combo (jet\u2011ski + banana boat, \u20b9\u202f1\u202f200). <br>*Luxury*: Full\u2011day water\u2011sports (incl. windsurf, scuba intro) \u2013 \u20b9\u202f3\u202f000. |\\n| **15:30 \u2013 16:30** | **Coffee/Refreshments** | Caf\u00e9 at Vagator \u2013 \u20b9\u202f150. |\\n| **16:30 \u2013 18:00** | **Visit Chapora Fort & Sunset at Vagator** | Free entry, spectacular views. |\\n| **18:30 \u2013 20:00** | **Early Dinner / Snacks** | *Budget*: Local dhaba (prawn curry, \u20b9\u202f300). <br>*Mid*: Gunpowder (South Indian\u2011Goan, \u20b9\u202f1\u202f000). <br>*Luxury*: Sunset dinner on a private yacht (\u20b9\u202f4\u202f500). |\\n| **20:30** | **Return to hotel, collect luggage** | |\\n| **21:00 \u2013 22:00** | **Transfer to Dabolim Airport** | Pre\u2011booked taxi/limo (see transport). |\\n| **23:30** | **Flight home** | Safe travels! |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## How to Stay Within **\u20b9\u202f50\u202f000**  \\n\\n1. **Choose the Mid\u2011Range Plan** \u2013 total \u2248 **\u20b9\u202f20\u202f000** per person, leaving ~\u20b9\u202f30\u202f000 for extra splurges (spa, extra shopping, upgraded meals).  \\n2. **If you prefer Luxury** \u2013 trim about **\u20b9\u202f5\u202f200** by:  \\n   * Swapping the private yacht cruise for a sunset beach dinner (save ~\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000).  \\n   * Opting for a 4\u2011star resort (e.g., Alila, \u20b9\u202f12\u202f000/night) instead of The Leela (save ~\u20b9\u202f6\u202f000).  \\n   * Reducing the water\u2011sports package to a single activity (save ~\u20b9\u202f2\u202f000).  \\n\\n3. **Budget\u2011Only Option** \u2013 total \u2248 **\u20b9\u202f6\u202f350** \u2013 you could upgrade food or transport and still stay far under the limit, allowing a generous souvenir budget.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Quick Tips & Hacks  \\n\\n| Tip | Why it Helps |\\n|-----|--------------|\\n| **Book hotels & activities on **[Goibibo/MakeMyTrip]** 2\u20113 weeks in advance** | Prices drop 15\u201125\u202f% and you lock in the best rooms. |\\n| **Rent a scooter** (\u20b9\u202f400/day) **instead of taxis** for intra\u2011city travel | Saves ~\u20b9\u202f1\u202f200\u2011\u20b9\u202f1\u202f500 over two days. |\\n| **Carry a reusable water bottle** | Tap water is safe in most hotels; you\u2019ll avoid buying bottled water (\u20b9\u202f30\u202f/\u202fbottle). |\\n| **Use Paytm/Google Pay for small purchases** | Many beach shacks give a 5\u202f% discount for digital payments. |\\n| **Travel off\u2011peak (late\u2011Oct to early\u2011Nov)** | Hotel rates are ~30\u202f% lower and beaches are less crowded. |\\n| **Combine attractions** \u2013 e.g., Fort Aguada + lighthouse in one walk | Saves on transport and time. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Printable Summary (Mid\u2011Range Example)\\n\\n| Category | Cost (INR) |\\n|----------|------------|\\n| **Accommodation** (Novotel) | 10\u202f000 |\\n| **Food** | 3\u202f800 |\\n| **Transport** (scooter + airport taxi) | 2\u202f300 |\\n| **Attractions** (dolphin\u2011watch, water\u2011sports, sunset cruise) | 3\u202f900 |\\n| **Miscellaneous** | 1\u202f000 |\\n| **Grand Total** | **\u20b9\u202f20\u202f000** |\\n\\n> **You still have ~\u20b9\u202f30\u202f000** left in your \u20b9\u202f50\u202f000 budget \u2013 perfect for a spa day, a private dinner, extra shopping, or even extending your stay by a night!  \\n\\nEnjoy your Goa adventure! \ud83c\udf34\ud83c\udfd6\ufe0f\ud83d\udea4\",\"type\":\"TextMessage\"},\"inner_messages\":[]},\"name\":\"Travel_Planner\"}", "sender": "Travel_Planner_c42977c6-7a7f-478f-bc63-3cf37ebcbcb8/c42977c6-7a7f-478f-bc63-3cf37ebcbcb8", "receiver": null, "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.DELIVER", "type": "Message"}
